1037
01:18:43,582 --> 01:18:45,143
Are you okay?

1038
01:18:45,790 --> 01:18:47,448
What are you doing?

1039
01:18:47,550 --> 01:18:51,161
Watching the clock.
Ten minutes is long here.

1040
01:18:54,213 --> 01:18:55,555
"The king was pleased.

1041
01:18:55,652 --> 01:18:57,245
Thinking it over,

1042
01:18:57,332 --> 01:19:01,161
he approved of men
being responsible for what they ate.

1043
01:19:01,283 --> 01:19:04,131
After punishing him,
he said to the fisherman:

1044
01:19:04,219 --> 01:19:07,567
'Give a man a fish,
you feed him for a day.

1045
01:05:49,671 --> 01:19:10,883
Teach a man to fish and
you feed him for a lifetime.

1046
01:19:10,883 --> 01:19:13,184
Then the King disappeared."

1047
01:19:16,457 --> 01:19:20,035
Can we go home now?

1048
01:19:29,976 --> 01:19:32,975
I'm hungry!

1049
01:20:27,949 --> 01:20:29,159
Here.

1050
01:20:29,253 --> 01:20:33,596
Are you sure?
It won't be a fun trip.

1051
01:20:41,092 --> 01:20:43,033
Where did you get this?

1052
01:20:43,139 --> 01:20:45,343
In the library.

1053
01:20:45,435 --> 01:20:48,631
Where's your house?

1054
01:20:51,562 --> 01:20:54,115
You lived in the countryside,
like Mom?

1055
01:20:54,329 --> 01:20:58,323
It was more like a desert.

1056
01:24:04,810 --> 01:24:08,071
Long ago, my ancestors
tortured people on tables.

1057
01:24:08,250 --> 01:24:10,104
That's how we got our name.

1058
01:24:10,193 --> 01:24:11,818
"Mesa" is Spanish for "table."

1059
01:24:11,928 --> 01:24:14,350
They tortured them
in the house where you went?

1060
01:24:14,465 --> 01:24:15,741
No.

1061
01:24:15,825 --> 01:24:18,279
I don't know, maybe.
It's so sad.

1062
01:24:18,384 --> 01:24:21,678
Miss de la Mesa.
Repeat what I said.

1063
01:24:21,767 --> 01:24:24,135
"The goat was eaten
by the wolf for disobeying."

1064
01:24:24,247 --> 01:24:26,156
Sit down.

1065
01:24:26,247 --> 01:24:29,955
Getting eaten by the wolf
was its punishment.

1066
01:24:30,062 --> 01:24:32,745
So the text is about
the need for obedience.

1067
01:24:32,861 --> 01:24:34,235
Sister, I don't get it.

1068
01:24:34,326 --> 01:24:37,456
My grandpa showed me
the paw of a fox caught in a trap.

1069
01:24:37,549 --> 01:24:40,069
It gnawed off its paw to get free.

1070
01:24:40,164 --> 01:24:42,019
That's quite different.

1071
01:24:42,141 --> 01:24:45,555
The goat wasn't trapped.
Mr. Seguin fed it, loved it.

1072
01:24:45,652 --> 01:24:48,847
But he kept it tied up.
It's in the book.

1073
01:24:49,011 --> 01:24:51,880
Are you saying
the goat wanted to die?

1074
01:24:51,979 --> 01:24:53,123
That would be a sin.

1075
01:24:53,283 --> 01:24:54,111
Sit down.

1076
01:24:54,218 --> 01:24:56,803
Animals aren't Catholic, Sister.

1077
01:24:57,601 --> 01:24:59,968
What do you think it says?

1078
01:25:00,081 --> 01:25:02,699
The goat has two options:

1079
01:25:02,793 --> 01:25:05,639
To stay at Mr. Seguin's
or escape to the mountains.

1080
01:25:05,727 --> 01:25:08,062
It leaves,
thinking the wolf won't eat it.

1081
01:25:08,160 --> 01:25:09,566
Stand up to speak!

1082
01:25:09,680 --> 01:25:13,508
It goes up to the mountains,
hoping to become free.

1083
01:25:13,590 --> 01:25:15,795
Well, it was mistaken.
And so are you.

1084
01:25:15,919 --> 01:25:16,966
Sit down.

1085
01:25:17,119 --> 01:25:20,380
I'll get a bad grade
and lose my bonus points.

1086
01:25:20,477 --> 01:25:23,772
We think you were right.
Trust us.

1087
01:25:23,885 --> 01:25:26,536
You also say Snow White
and Mickey Mouse are fascists.

1088
01:25:26,629 --> 01:25:28,701
And the Americans, and napalm!

1089
01:25:28,788 --> 01:25:31,406
You make mistakes, like Dad did.

1090
01:25:31,507 --> 01:25:33,100
He said he did.

1091
01:25:33,211 --> 01:25:36,310
Yes, sometimes we're wrong.
So is your teacher.

1092
01:25:36,411 --> 01:25:39,444
So, no one's really sure
about anything?

1093
01:25:39,571 --> 01:25:41,228
What do you think?

1094
01:25:41,330 --> 01:25:45,127
Were you wrong about the goat?

1095
01:25:45,490 --> 01:25:46,700
Are you sure?

1096
01:25:46,793 --> 01:25:47,360
Yes.

1097
01:25:47,457 --> 01:25:48,984
You see.

1098
01:25:49,088 --> 01:25:51,510
I'm hungry.
Can we eat?

1099
01:25:51,617 --> 01:25:54,234
Yes, come help me.

1100
01:25:55,504 --> 01:25:58,121
Is that why you want
to change schools?

1101
01:25:58,224 --> 01:26:00,329
You won't see
your friend Cecile anymore.

1102
01:26:00,448 --> 01:26:03,742
It doesn't matter.
It's like changing nannies.

1103
01:26:03,831 --> 01:26:05,292
How?

1104
01:26:06,126 --> 01:26:07,532
It's sad when they leave,

1105
01:26:07,605 --> 01:26:12,013
but if the next one is nice,
it's okay.

1106
01:26:15,604 --> 01:26:18,452
Thanks.

1107
01:26:18,757 --> 01:26:21,407
Here we are!

1108
01:26:23,955 --> 01:26:26,857
It's like "Sundaying" on Wednesday!

1109
01:26:26,963 --> 01:26:28,817
Exactly!

1110
01:26:28,915 --> 01:26:30,027
Pasta!

1111
01:26:30,139 --> 01:26:31,829
Yes!

1112
01:16:58,606 --> 01:16:59,053
Wait, put this here.

1113
01:26:58,254 --> 01:27:01,319
<i>The Right To Live Differently</i>

1114
01:27:02,124 --> 01:27:07,688
<i>You're hearing the last speech</i>
<i>of President Salvador Allende,</i>

1115
01:27:07,812 --> 01:27:09,916
<i>who died during the coup in Chile,</i>

1116
01:27:09,995 --> 01:27:11,654
<i>last September 11.</i>

1117
01:27:11,756 --> 01:27:16,708
<i>I'll pay with my life</i>
<i>my loyalty to the people.</i>

1118
01:27:16,874 --> 01:27:21,631
<i>History is ours</i>
<i>and is made by the people.</i>

1119
01:27:21,755 --> 01:27:22,932
<i>Long live Chile!</i>

1120
01:27:23,034 --> 01:27:24,178
<i>Long live the people!</i>

1121
01:27:24,290 --> 01:27:26,394
<i>Long live the workers!</i>

1122
01:30:49,600 --> 01:30:52,120
For Elias

